articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israeli forces kept up bombardments across the enclave and blew up houses on its northern edge.
articles.title: Israeli strikes kill 15 in Gaza, Cairo holds fresh talks with Hamas

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: European Council president Antonio Costa and Kaja Kallas, the EU's foreign policy chief, arrived in the Ukrainian capital Kyiv on Sunday, using the first day in their new roles to send a message of support for Ukraine in its war with Russia.
articles.title: EU's new top foreign policy officials visit Ukraine in show of solidarity

articles.author: Luiza Ilie
articles.description: Romanians vote in a parliamentary election on Sunday in which the far right is expected to gain from uncertainty over whether the shock result in a presidential election will stand.
articles.title: Romania's far right expected to make gains in parliamentary election

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Cyclone Fengal killed at least 19 people in India and Sri Lanka and caused flooding in Tamil Nadu state and the Puducherry region after crossing India's southern coast from the Bay of Bengal on Saturday.
articles.title: Cyclone Fengal kills 19 in India and Sri Lanka

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin has approved a military focused budget for 2025-2027, a document published on the official legal acts website showed on Sunday.
articles.title: Putin approves military focused 2025-2027 budget

articles.author: Ben Blanchard, Roger Tung
articles.description: War has no winners and peace is priceless, Taiwan President Lai Ching-te said on Saturday in Hawaii after visiting a memorial to the attack on Pearl Harbor on a trip to the United States that has angered Beijing.
articles.title: War has no winners, Taiwan president says in visit to Hawaii

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China vowed "resolute countermeasures" on Sunday to a recently approved U.S. arms sale to Taiwan, saying it had lodged a complaint over the sale, which it said seriously infringes on China's sovereignty.
articles.title: China vows 'resolute countermeasures' after US arms sale to Taiwan

articles.author: Jessica Donati
articles.description:
Joe Biden
 sets off for Angola on Sunday on a trip that will deliver on a promise to visit Africa during his presidency and focus on a major, U.S.-backed railway project that aims to divert critical minerals away from China.
articles.title: Biden’s long-awaited Africa trip to tout a win against China

articles.author: Maayan Lubell
articles.description: Palestinian militant group Hamas released a video of an Israeli-American hostage on Saturday, in which he pleads for U.S. President-elect Donald Trump to secure his release.
articles.title: Hamas releases video of US-Israeli hostage in Gaza

articles.author: Mushtaq Ali, Charlotte Greenfield
articles.description: Deadly sectarian clashes have continued in Pakistan's north-western Kurram district in spite of a tentative ceasefire struck late last week, local officials said, with the death toll now over 130 as authorities try to broker a solution.
articles.title: Death toll in Pakistan sectarian clashes now over 130, official says
